You gain experience!!<br>
<br>
She gives you a 2 slot container that looks like a potion bottle, called the solvent of preservation.<br>
<br>
You say, ‘what night ember’<br>
Acolyte Xjari V’lyr says “Though you have earned some trust from us, outsider, I will only tell you this: There are three known surfaced quantities of this material and all three are carried by those loyal to Innoruk. The particular specimen we have been seeking is now held in the hands of a high priest, who we know from your efforts and Izeras note, was resold the item by Thiryn in the Tier’Dal and Ogre outpost of the Overthere. Go to Kunark and find the priest. Retrive the Night Ember Sphere by killing him in any means you deem necessary and then preserve the sphere within the potion I have already given you and return it to Izera.’<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=natal>natal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 11:35:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Primordial Malice (Izera N'kar) - Part 3</span><hr size=1> Now for the really fun part! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
The item you need is something called “imbued night ember sphere” which drops off High Priest X’Tir in the outpost at OT. Actually, according the beastiary on the allahkazam site, there is another new mob there as well named “Vazern Ith’taris” who drops the same item (although I have not personally confirmed that). Btw, he will respond to prompts, so he might be involved in a counter Primordial Malice quest (just a thought – maybe there is one). I found this to be the most challenging of the known steps in the quests. It seems these guys go out with the goons at night doing goonish things. They look like goons, but are lower level (~40 I would guess, blue to lvl 54) and do not run at jboot speed (Incidently, contrary to popular belief, goons do NOT run at sow speed. I agroed them a number of times on this quest, and used to hunt in OT and could always outrun them, even when they had been intially able to hit me – ie had been standing right next to me). As some of you may know, during the day the goons are stationed at particular positions in the outpost. X’Tir is just behind a column near the gap in the south wall, and Vazern in the building closest to that. The closest true goon is T’Vem, who is stationed next to the NE column of the pagoda thing in front of the main gates. This was quite a fair distance from X’Tir. I tried pulling X’Tir from the south gap, but on both occasions T’Vem agroed. Since he is much faster than X’Tir, there is not much hope of doing the little root and run method of splitting them – there is no time and he hits hard. When night falls, the goons go on patrol. They assemble in Vazern’s building (Vazern leaves and stands off a bit – don’t know why) and after a while they head out on patrol. This is your chance. The general and the real goons head off and split into pairs outside the fort. X’tir and Vazern lag a bit and then start killing stuff outside the main gates as they head south. This causes them to fall way behind. They are paired, but gradually drift apart, when they do, jump X’Tir and pull him to the wall where you can dispatch him. He does cast, but didn’t heal, at least when I killed him. He seemed to be doing smite type DDs only. A word to note, quite a few on my original spells were resisted, the initial slow as a pull, followed by a lot of roots. He also tended to break root pretty quickly. He didn’t do too much damage to my shaman, but I was fully buffed with resists and had regrowth up. Even so, the resists took their toll on my mana, and I was basically oom when he decided to turn and run. He didn’t hit particularly hard, up to about 80 max from what I can remember. Place the imbued night ember sphere in the solvent of preservation and you get preserved night ember. This is taken back to SRO and given to Izera.<br>
<br>
Izera N’Kar says “Excellent, outsider! Now, I trust you have retained the eroding solvent that I have given you. Use the solvent and the powdered Night ember I have given you when following [my instructions], then return the raw materials to Xjari.’<br>
